SONATA,Sedan,@stephenbiffar1607,"I have a 2024 sonata sel with the conv pckg.   Love this car and the 191 hp engine is a good engine. But here are my complaints.  In sport mode it runs to the very high end of the rpm range for that gear especially going up a hill.  I don’t use the shifters so a little annoying with the gear shifts.  If you back off the accelerator pedal a little then repress it shifts better.  I think it runs better if you use the normal mode But everytime you start the car, it reverts to sport mode.  I really don’t care for the forward-reverse park on the stick from the steering column.  The radio software is terrible.  Everytime you start the car. The radio goes to its initial start which means you have to hit media button 3-4 times to get to the radio listings, then be able to choose your favorites.  The radio Never goes back to where it was when you turned off the engine.  You would think Hyundai would update this through a download but never has.  My previous 2021 sonata had the turbo 4 cylinder engine which was a great engine but Hyundai stopped making it.",0,SONATA,0
