KONA,SUV,@joejoe-the-original,"@ 16:50 key separate from keyfob?  Nope that is not the worst thought in 2024 - it is the most reasonable and well thought out change.  Switchblade keyfobs are annoying and  Integrated mechanical keys in the keyfob when used frequently destroy the keyfob prematurely costing a huge amount of money to replace the keyfob.  I know of a  vehicle with the integrated key.  After destroying the first keyfob, the driver removed the key permanently from the second keyfob and put it separately on a keychain with the keyfob.  This saved them from destroying the second keyfob.  The protector on the mechanical key is a good idea,  it prevents one from scratching glasses in their pockets and their cellphone screens.  @ 17:25 Rear hatch kick sensor dance was hillarious and is pretty accurate.",1,KONA,4
