KONA,SUV,@axx8326,"He cannot spell it out for the masses so he puts it very politically correct. When a thing is junk ""it's interesting what they did here"" . The car is built in the typical fashion of the Koreans. Very nice/good-ish interiors with often very futuristic exterior designs (now the beauty is in the eyes of the beholder) that age rather poorly, The engine and transmission are at the bottom of their upgrade list and is always a gamble how long they will last. Some will get a lot of miles out of them without any major repairs some will be stuck with lemons whose transmissions and engines keep on dying.
The money and the choice are always yours to make an educated decision however before bashing the Koreans it's important to look around and realize that pretty much all the new(er) cars regardless of the manufacturer are meh and often times you are paying for a badge and not necessarily for the quality",5,KONA,0
