KONA,SUV,@Meows1212,"I was impressed when they gave this one as my rental car. The looks outside was not that bad, there is still that uniqueness looks into it and there's a big difference to that Pontiac that he showed; still respect his humble opinion. The best one is the interior and all the safety features that comes with it. Lane and Drive assist, is very helpful especially if you're on a long boring drive or if you're sight seeing and just want to have a minute peek of the view. It feels like Tesla's auto drive, same but different. Downside is the auto break (AEB) is not that smooth, feels like it hard break once it detected a car in front even though it is still far away. There is also some occasion that it will apply AEB and then slowly drives forward, which is strange. Almost has the luxurious features but cheap materials on it, not leathered nor any high quality dashboards, etc... Gas consumption in normal driving is efficiently acceptable but in sport mode was ridiculous, it hungers for gas.",0,KONA,0
