SONATA,Sedan,@ascott2168,"Folks, do yourselves a favor, get a Camry and go home!

I own a 2015 Sonata Limited 2.0T and I’ve gotten my oil changed every 3-5k miles (on avg, closer to 3k), I don’t drive like a teenager and I take care of the car overall. I bought it with 35k miles and I’m currently at 107,500. Issues,

Turbo replacement #1 - 88k miles. Took it to Midas (BIG MISTAKE). The manager did explain what happened  in detail and genuine Hyundai parts were used. Out of service for 4 days. Extended warranty paid for the bulk of the $3K bill.

Turbo replacement 2 - 95k miles. Turbo failed again and was leaking oil. Dealer fixed it & the same extended warranty company paid for the bulk of the bill. Same price.


97k miles - blower motor was acting intermittently causing the fan to not operate when needed ( it was hell to not have any airflow when it was 100 degrees outside). Took it to the dealer & of course it worked fine. It’s working 98% of the time now.

100k miles - Timing chain and tensioner were loose and had to be replaced. Extended warranty paid for the bulk of the repair.

103k - new struts and all associated parts

My next car will be a Camry, MDX, Pathfinder or an RX350. I dont want any headaches.",5,SONATA,0
