IONIQ 6,Sedan,@mglmouser,"You should check wether the RWD also has the tiny frunk.
On my RWD Ioniq5, it was shipped—as all North American models—with the small frunk from the AWD (extra motor cuts down on available room for a frunk).
I bought from Korea the normal Eruo/Asian RWD frunk, which takes the 26L to 54L, an actual useful size. Not cheap, but cheaper than motorcycle saddlebags, to put it in perspective.

The theory of why it shipped with the small frunk is the NA rules on vehicle escape requirements of having a button to open frunk. The  measure of it is apparently a 3 year old reference mannequin. But a few models were actually shipped in Quebec with the large frunk. So our assumption is just that Hyundai was cheaping out.",0,IONIQ 6,0
