IONIQ 6,Sedan,@wesleythompson451,"This is the easiest way to distinguish a sunroof from a moonroof.

Sunroof: a clear glass panel that can either open or not open for air. A sunroof will always have transparent glass and a completely opaque sliding panel to shield passengers from the light. The important part is that you either have full light or no light.

Moonroof: You can have partial light with a moonroof. Everything else is the same. Whether it can get full light or be fully shielded from light, if it's capable of partial light, it's a moonroof. A moonroof may use tinted glass or a mesh panel to achieve partial light.",0,IONIQ 6,4
IONIQ 6,Sedan,@scottnathanphoto,"I'm a design guy first and this is a looker, so emphatic yes.",0,IONIQ 6,4
IONIQ 6,Sedan,@MYJ61,"Historically in the auto industry, a sliding metal panel is a sunroof, but a sliding glass panel is a moon roof.",0,IONIQ 6,4
