IONIQ 6,Sedan,@dsp4392,"He's right the car looks sick, but not in a positive way . It literally looks like it's affected by a disease. I saw a few in person and I felt offended lol. Those swooping curves in the back made me nauseous. To each their own of course, but I can confidently say that it is one of the ugliest car to have ever been designed. Fiat Multiplas everywhere rejoice!

I remember when Hyundai unveiled this design along with the N Vision 74. Kind of a shame that they brought this ugly duckling to production while the gorgeous 74 remains a concept car. It's also quite disappointing that they didn't stick with the Ioniq5's design language. Not only was it much better looking (and a breath of fresh air in an endless sea of flabby bean, angry fascia designs), but having a unified design language across would've strengthened the brand.

The 6 makes Hyundai's design department look like they have no idea what they're doing and are just throwing pasta at the wall to see what sticks.",1,IONIQ 6,0
