AVANTE,Sedan,@dragonfang8670,"People really don't give this car the praise it deserves. Unfortunately most new ""car enthusiasts"" are also brainwashed into measuring their Horse Power and looking for ways to ""smoke"" the competition on the highway. At the end of the day, the Elantra N, the i30N, and the i20N are incredible cars. Sure, they haven't got the luxury of an AMG A45, or an Audi RS3, but they're more fun to drive. 

I am fortunate enough to own three cars. A Peugeot RCZ, a Porsche Cayman and an i30N hatch. I can tell you, that from a driving perspective, the i30N is genuinely more fun that the RCZ or the Cayman. There's just something about the car that makes you love it when you drive it.",1,ELANTRA,4
AVANTE,Sedan,@caseybonnette2151,"One thing to note with the EN is octane learning. On a fresh tank of gas and without completing the proper drive cycle, the EN will build 3-4 pounds less boost than when its learned. Its a noticable difference from the drivers seat. Could possibly account for such a big gap between last years and this years. 18-19 pounds once learned otherwise youre getting 14-15 pounds",5,ELANTRA,4
