AVANTE,Sedan,@youareallbots,"I owned an Elantra N, and I absolutely loved it......... for the first 20,000 miles. I started having misfiring issues. It turned out to be a fuel injector. The dealer had my car for several weeks because apparently nobody stocks anything. I got it back, literally a month later, the same thing happened again. The dealer would not pay for a rental car, I was constantly getting the runaround. And after doing my own research I found out that the fuel injectors are a bit of a weak Link in these cars and they can just leave you stranded at any time. I had a couple other issues and at that point said screw this and traded it in for a Toyota. I love the improvements Hyundai has made over the last several years, but it seems like they still have a little work to do in my opinion.",3,ELANTRA,0
