AVANTE,Sedan,@joshblck1,"I've had my EN for a little over a year now and its got 51k miles. Never had a single issue with it and it's so much fun to drive. What I don't get is that some people and reviewers say that the Type R is a good bit further ahead performance wise and from what I've seen they are really really close. It's like people are afraid to put the EN next to the Type R in fear of the backlash they will get for comparing what used to be one of the worst car brands to one of the best. 0-60 times are pretty much dead even ( with the EN having the slightest advantage in the dct ) and track times seem to be pretty dead even too ( they seem to trade blows depending on the type of track and transmission ). 

Don't get me wrong, I'd pick the Type R as well just cause I prefer the styling and I'm a Honda fan but when the time came to make my purchase the Type R had massive dealer mark ups and I wanted a DCT for commuting purposes. 

My point is that where performance is concerned, they are so close that it's time to stop putting the Type R on a pedestal and see them as true equals.",1,ELANTRA,0
