AVANTE,Sedan,@justwingingit1,"Just Googled Elantra N reliability issues and a Reddit laundry list of quality issues came up(fit,trim,etc.).Having said that…the post stated that as far as engine failures on cars that were unmodified…very hard to find/non-existent. Seems promising but like I said…there are random quality issues from not only the past but as recent as 2023…one of which had to with high pressure car wash’s affecting under hood sensors/putting car into limp mode. I love the DCT N option and am tempted everytime I see a positive review BUT warranty or not…having a car no matter how much fun randomly blindsiding you with this issue or that…more than likely at the worst possible time…just isn’t worth it…no matter how much of a bargain it is. I’ve owned FK8s with zero issues and other Hondas with mileage over 350k mileage that still didn’t have one drop of oil underneath them. I realize the price difference but Honda usually over engineers it’s cars and to someone like me who keeps his cars for 15-20 years…that price difference/peace of mind is worth it. As a side note…unfortunately Toyota’s vehicles have not been as reliable as they have been in the past otherwise I’d be looking harder a the GR Corolla(Auto) or the future MR2/Celica with the upcoming 400hp Turbo 4. Hopefully the recent quality control issues will be reigned in before their release…",0,ELANTRA,2
