TUCSON,SUV,@chrisd1328,"Bought a 2024 Tucson SEL Convenience Package for my wife & she loves it.  I also watch your videos all the time and appreciate your reviews.  
I'm a retired engineer who enjoys doing the basic maintenance on my vehicles.  I would add 2 comments to your review:  #1) Hyundai makes it super easy for the DIY'er to change the transmission fluid.   You have to take off the plastic shroud & there is a magnetic drain plug with a plastic overflow plug on the side.  It is also a cast aluminum housing which is great for heat dissipation.  It does shift great.  #2) I'm surprised you didn't comment on the rear wiper.  It is mounted high & concealed.  The wiper is totally out of the weather & fresh when you need to use it.  We looked at Honda CRV's ( a 6' tall guy hits his head in the back seat ), Toyota RAV 4, The tablet is goofy, raised up it blocks your view & a Subaru Outback, very nice & safe but compare changing spark plugs in the Subaru vs. this Tucson.  I would also add the Adaptive Cruise & driving assist work very well on our Tucson.  It's a great road trip car for a couple + if you drive 75 mph we are getting  32 mpg which I can live with.
Great review.  Thanks",14,TUCSON,4
