TUCSON,SUV,@lindsaydale3246,"I own a 2025 Hybrid Tuscon and a 2022 Hybrid Yaris Cross. I got rid of a 2006 Prius when I bought the Tuscon.  The reason I bought the Tuscon and not the RAV4 is the horrible droning of Toyota Hybrids at highway speeds.  The Tuscon, because of its traditional automatic paired with the electic motor makes it much quieter and a whole lot more responsive in overtaking. Test drove the RAV4 on the highway and the Tuson was considerably better.  The seats are    Alcantara and not leather which is much better on long drives in the Australian heat. If the car was going to be used mostly around town, then the RAV4 is better in the urban environment. The quality of the components seems to be on par with Toyota now and there is less flex in the dash and console on the Korean built Hyundai compared to the Japanese built Toyota.

I am surprised that North America does not get the Yaris Cross as it is smaller outside but larger inside than the Corolla Hatch and is very economical. Without trying, we get  3.5 to 4.4 l/100kms around town. (67 to 52 MPG).",11,TUCSON,0
