TUCSON,SUV,@wladimirb1506,"Leased a 2026 Hyundai Tucson N-Line X 1.6 150 hp FWD petrol since 11/25, driven 3,000 km so far:

Pros: great design, excellent interior quality (N-Line), lots of space, good acceleration, top-notch infotainment, strong matrix headlights, very good Krell sound system, comfortable seats, and the panoramic roof is a nice touch. The suspension feels nicely agile without being floaty, yet still very composed on rough roads.

Cons: fuel consumption is higher than expected: around 9 l/100 km mixed, 6.0 l/100 km is possible at 100 km/h, but on longer motorway trips at 130 km/h it’s hardly ever below 8.5 l/100 km. The lane-keeping assist keeps the car too far to the left, which feels uncomfortable. The automatic transmission reacts slowly: shifting from D to R feels like it takes 1.5–2 seconds, and when pulling away there’s first a short delay, then a sudden, jerky surge of power. The throttle is also tuned very aggressively in the 0–20 km/h range. Maybe it will improve as the system adapts, but right now it still feels rather poor.

Conclusion: I would choose it again. For me, the overall balance works.",0,TUCSON,0
