TUCSON,SUV,@jeffmorse645,"I have a 2023 Limited FWD (live in Florida - it's fine) with the 2.5 naturally aspirated engine. It's no barn-burner by any stretch, but it gets me around town just fine and can enter an interstate without drama. In my mix of city and highway driving I get about 28 MPG. On the highway it's really good. At a steady 70 MPH I get 35-36 MPG. Also, there are no rattles, squeaks or buzzes in the interior trim. My previous car was a 2021 Subaru Legacy and that was the biggest rattle trap I've ever own. Constantly chasing and trying to fix interior noises. The Hyundai seems much more solid and better put together at least from the interior trim. All in all it's a comfortable, economical, easy to live with crossover. Almost forgot to mention, the AC is very strong and the Bose sound system is great.",1,TUCSON,4
