TUCSON,SUV,@Brywassoldalemon,"I owned a 2020 Tucson SEL from brand new. Sold it in pristine condition with 28,000 miles a few months ago. It was so-so. Very lacking in horsepower and rarely got more than 20mpg even though I drove it like a baby. Didn’t care for the lower quality transmission. Liked that it had a timing chain. Mysteriously, about every five months vehicle would act like it didn’t want to start…always started but acted like it didn’t want to and it wasn’t cold out. BUT, what was hated and why I will NEVER do business w Hyundai again was the way the dealer treated my vehicle when it was getting serviced. My vehicle was returned to me with grease all over it, a missing piece (they took four months getting it back to me) a tire w 23 pounds of pressure (they punctured it and refused to take accountability), and four indentations in front passenger seat that were permanent. They refused to tell me WHAT extremely heavy object they placed inside on the seat to damage it. I had to pay to get it professionally detailed and fix the tire. It was an AWD so getting one new tire was not an option. Contacted Hyundai Client Relations to make a complaint but they were WORTHLESS and dismissive. I told them I was DONE with Hyundai after buying two Hyundai’s in six years and they could have cared less. I bought a 2026 Camry and they had better treat me better.",0,TUCSON,0
