TUCSON,SUV,@toddschrocatart,"My wife had the GV 70 with the big engine and the really nice interior package. We got the Tucson SEL convenience package and we love it. One of the things you didn’t talk about where the reclining backseats. I have an Acura RDX and it has amazing room in the backseat And most SUVs in this size range do not this one actually does it’s comparable to my RDX.  The stereo isn’t as good as my car, but it’s sufficient and having the Bluetooth Apple CarPlay is a very convenient and to us important feature. The interior is very quiet and while not as quiet as the genesis it’s pretty damn close I’m glad one of the manufacturers is stepping up to make a car that might last longer because the trend has been the other direction, especially with Toyota building and planned obsolescence Removed us as a customer. Our last six cars prior to these were Toyota‘s. We won’t go near them unless they fix their problems and it doesn’t look like they’re gonna fix them anytime soon.",0,TUCSON,0
