INSTER,SUV,@Car-crazy,"Finally a manufacturer that is listening to what people want, a simple basic car that will get you from A to B without all the electric bs and it has physical controls for everything. The only problem is that it is an ev. They need to put a small 1L or 1.2L petrol or diesel engine in this, and it will sell like got cakes. Having said that, a small cheap ev like this could make for a good city car. Because regardless of ev or engine no one is going to go long distance in this little car.
Evs normally have crap styling, but this actually doesn't look too bad. It is not the sort of car I would go for, I have a Land Cruiser, Jimny and a BMW road car so doesn't appeal to me in that sense, but I think a lot of people into regular cars will buy this.
Other manufacturers need to stop producing cars with all this stupid automated touch control everything crap and go back to basics. Modern retro is the way to go. No one needs lane keep assist or auto braking, etc. If people need or want them systems then they obviously can not drive and should not be on the road.",2,INSTER,0
